-- Yen Drops to 30-Month Low on Speculation of More Easing
-- B y   G r e g   S t o r e y
-- 2013-01-10T21:43:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-10/yen-drops-to-30-month-low-on-speculation-of-more-easing.html
The yen slid to the weakest level
since July 2010 against the dollar after a Nikkei report quoted
Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe as saying the central bank
should include maximum employment among its goals.  The yen has plunged since the election of Abe, who has
pledged to increase monetary stimulus to weaken the currency.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Greg Storey at 
 gstorey@bloomberg.net  